WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:11.040
Mr. Bean. By Richard Curtis and Robin Driscoll. Chapter 1. A great day.

00:11.040 --> 00:25.400
It was a stupid idea. Or was it? Mr. Bean in America. Two long months without the man.

00:25.400 --> 00:33.240
He at the Grierson Art Gallery in Los Angeles was very excited. George Grierson, the boss,

00:33.240 --> 00:39.880
stood outside the gallery and looked at the people in front of him. He smiled and turned

00:39.880 --> 00:50.200
to the cameras. This is a great day for the Grierson Gallery and a great day for America,

00:50.520 --> 00:58.040
he said. In two weeks, the most famous painting by an American artist is coming back home.

00:58.040 --> 01:08.040
Yes, everybody. America's most wonderful painting, Whistler's Mother, will be here in my gallery.

01:08.040 --> 01:18.400
At the National Gallery in London, everybody was very excited too. The Grierson Gallery wanted

01:18.400 --> 01:25.920
somebody from London to go to America for two months. They wanted a top man from the National

01:25.920 --> 01:34.000
Gallery to talk to people about the artist Whistler and his famous painting of his mother. Who was

01:34.000 --> 01:44.000
the right person for the job? Dr. Rosenblum or Dr. Cutler? At a meeting in one of the rooms in

01:44.000 --> 01:52.160
the gallery, everybody wanted to go. But first, they had to discuss a more important problem,

01:52.960 --> 02:01.040
Mr. Bean. Nobody in the room liked Mr. Bean. They all wanted him to leave the gallery.

02:02.320 --> 02:09.280
Why? What was wrong with the man? He only had to sit in one of the rooms in the gallery all day

02:09.280 --> 02:19.120
and watch the paintings. He wasn't very good at his job. He usually fell asleep. But why did they all

02:19.120 --> 02:28.000
hate him? Suddenly, the National Gallery's boss, Mr. Walton, came into the room and sat down at the

02:28.000 --> 02:35.760
table. We're talking about that strange man, Mr. Bean, sir, somebody said.

02:36.960 --> 02:45.680
We all think, be quiet, shouted Mr. Walton angrily. There's nothing wrong with Mr. Bean.

02:46.480 --> 02:52.320
He's a wonderful young man, one of the best men in the gallery.

02:53.280 --> 03:05.920
Nobody in the room said a word. They all looked very unhappy. Wait a minute. Somebody suddenly shouted.

03:05.920 --> 03:18.800
Of course. Why don't we send Mr. Bean to the Grierson Gallery in America? Nobody spoke. It was a stupid idea.

03:18.800 --> 03:29.520
It was a stupid idea. Or was it, Mr. Bean, in America, two long months without the man.

03:30.640 --> 03:40.160
Yes, yes, they all shouted. That's a great idea. Mr. Walton looked very happy. Right,

03:40.800 --> 03:50.400
don't sit there. Get Mr. Bean quickly. Mr. Bean sat and waited outside the room.

03:52.080 --> 04:01.920
Why did these important people want to see him? Suddenly, he sneezed loudly. He took out a paper

04:01.920 --> 04:13.360
handkerchief and blew his nose. Then he blew it again. Then again, more loudly, the noisiest

04:13.360 --> 04:24.960
nose blow in the world. Mr. Walton called Mr. Bean into the room. When he walked in, he smiled at

04:25.040 --> 04:33.920
everybody. They all looked at him and started laughing. Mr. Bean looked very stupid.

04:35.600 --> 04:39.360
Excuse me, Mr. Bean, Mr. Walton said.

04:42.880 --> 04:49.840
Something's coming out of your nose. It was some of his paper handkerchief.

04:50.720 --> 04:58.480
It looked very funny. Mr. Bean's face went red and he quickly pulled the paper out of his nose.

05:00.000 --> 05:11.680
Now, Mr. Bean, we want to ask you something. It's important and very exciting. Would you like to go to

05:11.760 --> 05:12.480
America?

05:18.000 --> 05:21.680
Chapter Two, an accident on the plane.

05:24.480 --> 05:33.760
With the bag in one hand and a big smile on his face, Mr. Bean hit it hard. Bang.

05:34.640 --> 05:45.920
America. Shouted Mr. Bean at the airport. I'm going to America.

05:47.120 --> 05:54.560
With a big smile on his face, he got on the plane and took out his camera. This was the beginning

05:54.560 --> 06:01.360
of his holiday and he wanted to take photos of everybody and everything.

06:02.000 --> 06:11.360
He found his seat next to another man, Mr. Tucker. Mr. Bean sat down and took a photo of him, too.

06:12.880 --> 06:23.760
Mr. Tucker stopped reading his newspaper and looked at him angrily. Then he stood up and quickly moved to the seat in front of him.

06:24.320 --> 06:31.680
He didn't like strange people and Mr. Bean was very strange.

06:31.680 --> 06:43.360
Happy in his new seat, Mr. Tucker fell asleep. Behind him, Mr. Bean couldn't sleep. He was too excited.

06:43.360 --> 06:52.720
He smiled at a woman with a young boy, but she didn't smile at him. My son's feeling

06:53.600 --> 07:02.720
sick, she said. Oh dear, said Mr. Bean. He was happy and he wanted other people to be happy, too.

07:04.880 --> 07:13.120
When the boy looked across at him, Mr. Bean took the last sweet from a bag. He threw it into the air

07:14.160 --> 07:21.840
and caught it in his mouth. Did the boy think it was clever? No.

07:23.520 --> 07:31.200
Did the boy laugh or smile? He did not. He looked strangely at Mr. Bean.

07:33.440 --> 07:39.200
Mr. Bean thought for a minute. Then he put the sweet bag up to his mouth

07:40.000 --> 07:49.280
and began to blow into it. He wanted to blow air into the bag and then break it with a loud noise.

07:50.240 --> 07:53.760
Bang! Everybody laughs at that.

07:55.680 --> 07:59.920
But there was something wrong with the bag and the air got out again.

08:01.600 --> 08:10.000
The boy's face was grey now and he felt very sick. Then he saw a white paper bag in the back

08:10.000 --> 08:17.760
of the seat in front of him. He took it out and opened it. Mr. Bean watched him.

08:18.560 --> 08:27.600
His eyes opened wide. Yes, yes, that bag was OK. He turned away and laughed.

08:28.400 --> 08:34.880
He's a clever boy. He remembered the bag in the back of the seat, he thought.

08:38.320 --> 08:45.200
But Mr. Bean looked away at the wrong time. The boy opened the bag quickly

08:46.080 --> 08:54.160
and was sick into it. Mr. Bean didn't see him. A minute later,

08:54.160 --> 09:00.160
before the boy could stop him, Mr. Bean took the bag. He quickly blew into it.

09:01.440 --> 09:09.200
Then he put it in front of Mr. Tucker's face. With the bag in one hand and a big smile on his face,

09:09.840 --> 09:19.040
Mr. Bean hit it hard. Bang! Mr. Tucker was not a happy man.

09:21.760 --> 09:28.960
Some time later, the plane arrived in Los Angeles. Mr. Bean looked at the people in the airport.

09:29.440 --> 09:35.760
I'm in America. He thought, this is wonderful.

09:38.000 --> 09:43.840
He started taking photos again. Near a wall, there were two policemen.

09:45.440 --> 09:54.880
Mr. Bean watched them and then he saw their guns. He thought of a game and smiled.

09:55.680 --> 10:01.760
He put one hand slowly inside his jacket and looked for his gun.

10:03.360 --> 10:09.680
Not really. Mr. Bean didn't have a gun, of course. He only wanted to play a game.

10:11.680 --> 10:20.320
The two policemen suddenly turned and saw him. They stopped talking and looked carefully at Mr. Bean.

10:21.200 --> 10:26.960
What was this little man's game? Did he have a gun?

10:28.880 --> 10:34.560
Quick! Said one of the policemen. He's got a gun! Get him!

10:36.320 --> 10:42.080
Mr. Bean gave them a smile. Then he turned and ran the other way fast.

10:43.600 --> 10:48.400
Everybody on the floor! Now! shouted the policeman.

10:50.320 --> 10:54.800
Everybody in the airport was afraid. People fell to the ground.

10:56.560 --> 10:59.680
Mr. Bean saw them and fell to the ground too.

11:01.360 --> 11:05.120
Not you, stupid! A man next to him said.

11:06.240 --> 11:12.640
Oh, thank you. Said Mr. Bean. He got up and started to run away again.

11:12.880 --> 11:20.960
But the policeman ran faster and caught him. They stood in front of him with their guns in his face.

11:22.160 --> 11:31.200
Slowly, take out your gun. They told him. Put it on the floor and stand back.

11:32.720 --> 11:39.120
Mr. Bean was very afraid. He carefully put his hand in his jacket

11:39.280 --> 11:42.960
and took out his two fingers.

11:44.640 --> 11:50.720
It was only a game. He said. I haven't really got a gun.

11:52.880 --> 11:58.160
The policeman looked at him. Who was this strange little man?

11:59.200 --> 12:06.160
Get out of here. They shouted angrily. Mr. Bean got out fast.

12:09.760 --> 12:14.640
Chapter three. Wet trousers.

12:17.040 --> 12:25.360
He saw a fan. R. He got up and moved slowly across the room.

12:26.720 --> 12:30.880
Then he started dancing in front of the fan.

12:33.680 --> 12:36.480
The Langleys were usually a very happy family.

12:37.120 --> 12:45.200
They lived in a large house in Los Angeles. David Langley had an important job at the Grierson Gallery.

12:46.400 --> 12:53.520
His wife, Alison, was a friendly, intelligent woman. They had two lovely children.

12:54.880 --> 13:00.160
A 15-year-old daughter, Jennifer, and a seven-year-old son, Kevin.

13:00.320 --> 13:05.680
One day, David came home from the gallery and said to his family,

13:06.080 --> 13:15.120
Listen, I've got a great idea. A top man from the National Gallery in London is coming to Los Angeles.

13:15.120 --> 13:20.240
I'd like to invite him here. He can stay with us for two months.

13:21.200 --> 13:24.800
David's family didn't like the idea very much.

13:25.040 --> 13:31.360
Who was this man? A boring Englishman? No, thank you.

13:31.360 --> 13:36.800
Here, in our house, for two months, Alison said,

13:36.800 --> 13:45.600
No, David. He can stay in a hotel. I'd like it. David answered angrily.

13:45.600 --> 13:51.520
He's a very intelligent man. It'll be good for all of us.

13:51.520 --> 13:59.040
So, Alison Langley and the children waited for the Englishman's visit.

14:01.920 --> 14:07.600
The big day arrived. Mr. Bean was late, problems with the police at the airport.

14:08.800 --> 14:15.200
But now he was here in the Langley's sitting room. They all looked at him and smiled.

14:16.000 --> 14:21.520
He didn't look very intelligent. He looked very strange.

14:22.720 --> 14:28.800
Was there something wrong with him? Perhaps he was tired after the long journey from England.

14:31.440 --> 14:35.120
The next morning, David took Mr. Bean to the Grierson Gallery.

14:36.640 --> 14:42.640
My boss, Mr. Grierson, would like to meet you at nine o'clock, he told Mr. Bean in the car.

14:43.600 --> 14:46.800
And he gets angry when people are late, Dr. Bean.

14:50.880 --> 14:53.840
Mr. Bean sat in the car and looked out of the window.

14:55.280 --> 15:04.240
Why did David call him Dr. Bean, not Mr. Bean? Dr was the name for the top men in the National

15:04.240 --> 15:12.160
Gallery, Dr. Rosenblum and Dr. Cutler. They were very intelligent and knew a lot about art.

15:13.280 --> 15:20.720
He didn't know anything about art. But he felt very important when David called him Dr. Bean.

15:22.800 --> 15:29.120
When they got to the gallery, Mr. Bean wanted to go to the toilet. David looked at his watch.

15:30.720 --> 15:38.560
The men's room is over there, Dr. Bean. But please, don't be too long. Mr. Grierson's waiting.

15:39.120 --> 15:46.320
Mr. Bean walked into the men's room. He went to the toilet, and then started to wash his hands.

15:47.320 --> 15:52.320
But the water went everywhere, over the front of his trousers.

15:53.920 --> 16:03.120
Oh, no, he thought. What am I going to do? I can't meet Mr. Grierson with wet trousers.

16:04.400 --> 16:07.120
Then he saw a machine on the wall.

16:07.760 --> 16:15.440
Ah, good. A hand dryer, he thought. That'll dry them in no time.

16:17.040 --> 16:25.920
Mr. Bean jumped up and down. But the machine was too high. The warm air didn't blow onto his trousers.

16:27.200 --> 16:36.160
Then he had an idea. He climbed onto a chair in front of the machine and started to move slowly

16:37.120 --> 16:43.840
from left to right. The warm air blew onto his trousers in the right place.

16:46.400 --> 16:53.040
Suddenly, a man came out of one of the toilets. He looked up and saw Mr. Bean.

16:54.480 --> 16:57.040
Then he walked out as fast as possible.

16:59.200 --> 17:05.680
David Langley stood outside the men's room and waited for Mr. Bean. He looked at his watch,

17:06.560 --> 17:08.080
it was after nine o'clock.

17:09.040 --> 17:15.760
Dr. Bean, we're late, he shouted. Mr. Grierson will be very angry.

17:17.840 --> 17:25.600
Mr. Bean came out of the men's room and followed David. This wasn't funny. His trousers weren't

17:25.600 --> 17:33.360
dry. He wanted more time in front of the hand dryer. He couldn't go into Mr. Grierson's office

17:33.360 --> 17:43.200
with wet trousers. Then he saw a newspaper on a table. He took the paper and put it in front of

17:43.200 --> 17:54.240
his trousers. Mr. Grierson's office was a beautiful room. There were paintings everywhere

17:54.880 --> 17:59.680
and on the wall behind the desk was a big poster of Whistler's mother.

18:00.480 --> 18:07.360
There were a lot of important people in the room. Mr. Grierson looked at his watch.

18:08.800 --> 18:18.000
Oh, David, good morning. And this is our famous Dr. Bean from England. How are you, Dr. Bean?

18:19.200 --> 18:26.640
Mr. Bean said hello to everybody in the room. Now, sit down, Dr. Bean. Said Mr. Grierson and took

18:26.720 --> 18:35.200
the newspaper out of his hands. Mr. Bean sat down quickly. He didn't want these important people

18:35.200 --> 18:43.760
to see his wet trousers. Everybody sat around the table and the meeting began. But Mr. Bean

18:43.760 --> 18:50.240
didn't listen to a word. He couldn't stop thinking about his trousers. What could he do?

18:50.640 --> 19:03.680
He saw a fan. He got up and moved slowly across the room. Then he started dancing in front of the fan.

19:05.680 --> 19:13.040
Everybody in the room stopped talking and looked at him. What is the man doing, they thought?

19:13.360 --> 19:23.280
Mr. Bean looked down at his trousers. Good, they were dry. He turned round and smiled at everybody.

19:24.640 --> 19:31.120
Then he walked slowly back to his seat. He wanted them to see the front of his lovely dry trousers.

19:32.080 --> 19:46.320
Yes, right. Dr. Bean said Mr. Grierson, please sit down. Now, when Whistler's mother arrives at the gallery,

19:46.320 --> 19:56.560
we want you to say something. About 20 minutes will be fine. You know, talk about the artist and his work, okay?

19:57.360 --> 20:05.680
Mr. Bean didn't understand him. Say something. But he didn't know anything about art.

20:05.680 --> 20:19.760
Yes, of course, he said. The meeting ended and everybody stood up. Mr. Grierson talked quietly to David.

20:20.560 --> 20:27.360
This, Dr. Bean, David, is the National Gallery's top man, right?

20:28.560 --> 20:38.560
That's right, sir. David answered. Good. This painting, Whistler's mother, is very important to the gallery.

20:38.560 --> 20:46.960
You know that. I don't want anything to go wrong. Do you understand me, David?

20:47.920 --> 20:56.320
I understand, sir, said David. He smiled at his boss, but he didn't feel very happy.

21:01.440 --> 21:04.400
Chapter 4. At the Fairground

21:07.120 --> 21:16.320
He sat down and started to work on the computers. The ride will be really dangerous now. He laughed.

21:17.920 --> 21:21.840
That evening, David came home and walked into the kitchen.

21:21.840 --> 21:26.400
Hi, Allie, he said, and put his arm around his wife.

21:26.400 --> 21:33.680
Hi, and said Alison. She looked behind David carefully and then smiled.

21:33.680 --> 21:41.280
Oh, good. No, Dr. Bean. I didn't like having that man in our house, dear.

21:41.520 --> 21:49.920
Ah, he isn't here now, but I'm sorry, dear. He's coming, said David.

21:50.960 --> 21:56.560
What? Jennifer, Kevin? Alison shouted. It's Plan B.

21:58.400 --> 22:05.120
What's Plan B, Allie? Asked David. Plan B is this, David, Alison said.

22:05.680 --> 22:10.720
The children and I are not going to stay in the same house as Dr. Bean.

22:10.720 --> 22:19.440
He's too strange. He makes funny faces. He throws sweets up in the air and catches them in his mouth.

22:19.440 --> 22:27.600
He broke my best picture. He's a very dangerous little man. We're going to my mothers for the weekend.

22:28.480 --> 22:34.800
But Allie, wait a minute. David cried, but he was too late.

22:34.800 --> 22:40.640
Alison and the two children were in her car. He watched them drive away.

22:40.640 --> 22:50.400
Oh, no. He thought, Dr. Bean will be here all weekend and I'll have no help from anybody.

22:51.200 --> 22:57.040
The next day was Saturday, and Mr. Bean wanted to see Los Angeles.

22:57.040 --> 23:01.200
When he got into David's car, he took out his camera.

23:01.200 --> 23:07.840
Great. He shouted excitedly. I'm going to enjoy today.

23:07.840 --> 23:14.480
David drove through the city, and Mr. Bean took photos of everything and everybody.

23:14.480 --> 23:22.480
People, buildings, policemen, dogs, trees, flowers. He was very busy.

23:22.480 --> 23:28.480
Then he put the camera up in front of David's face and took some photos of him too.

23:28.480 --> 23:34.480
Stop that, shouted David. It's dangerous. I'm trying to drive.

23:34.480 --> 23:40.480
In the afternoon, they stopped at a fairground in Santa Monica near Los Angeles.

23:40.480 --> 23:46.480
There were rides and sweet shops and people in funny hats.

23:46.480 --> 23:50.480
Mr. Bean bought an ice cream and a hat.

23:50.480 --> 23:56.480
Oh, this is wonderful. He shouted, and he took more and more photos.

23:56.480 --> 24:06.480
Look, David. That ride says really dangerous. Let's go on that.

24:06.480 --> 24:14.480
The ride was very exciting. It went up and down very fast.

24:14.480 --> 24:20.480
Everybody cried and shouted. David was afraid.

24:20.480 --> 24:26.480
That wasn't really dangerous. It was really boring.

24:26.480 --> 24:32.480
Mr. Bean said at the end. They left the ride and walked past the machine room.

24:33.480 --> 24:39.480
Mr. Bean saw the computers and machines in the room and had an idea.

24:39.480 --> 24:47.480
David, let's go on that ride again. He said, go and buy some more tickets.

24:47.480 --> 24:53.480
Okay, said David unhappily. He felt sick and wanted to go home.

24:53.480 --> 25:00.480
Mr. Bean walked into the machine room. Good. Nobody there.

25:00.480 --> 25:05.480
He sat down and started to work on the computers.

25:05.480 --> 25:11.480
The ride will be really dangerous now. He laughed.

25:11.480 --> 25:18.480
Some minutes later, David and Mr. Bean were in their seats again, ready for the same ride.

25:18.480 --> 25:25.480
And this time everybody was really afraid. People flew out of their seats into the air.

25:25.480 --> 25:28.480
But Mr. Bean enjoyed every minute of it.

25:28.480 --> 25:34.480
When they got off the ride, he looked at David. David's face was green.

25:34.480 --> 25:42.480
That was great. Laughs, Mr. Bean. Those computers are much better now.

25:42.480 --> 25:46.480
But he didn't see the policeman behind him.

25:46.480 --> 25:52.480
Later that afternoon in the police station, Mr. Bean stopped laughing.

25:52.480 --> 25:57.480
What did you do to those computers, you stupid little man?

25:57.480 --> 26:02.480
The policeman shouted, you hurt a lot of people.

26:02.480 --> 26:06.480
Mr. Bean looked down at the floor and said nothing.

26:06.480 --> 26:10.480
The policeman walked angrily out of the room.

26:10.480 --> 26:14.480
Mr. Bean looked up and saw a mirror.

26:14.480 --> 26:21.480
He stood up and started dancing in front of it. Then he made funny faces.

26:21.480 --> 26:26.480
But it was a two-way mirror. In the next room, the policeman and David

26:26.480 --> 26:30.480
stood behind the mirror and watched Mr. Bean.

26:30.480 --> 26:34.480
You say he's a top man from the National Gallery in London?

26:34.480 --> 26:36.480
Asked the policeman.

26:36.480 --> 26:40.480
Ah, yes, said David.

26:40.480 --> 26:43.480
And he's very intelligent?

26:43.480 --> 26:49.480
Yes, he doesn't look very intelligent to me.

26:49.480 --> 26:54.480
He said the policeman. He looks very, very stupid.

26:54.480 --> 26:59.480
Now get him out of here, fast!

27:02.480 --> 27:07.480
Chapter 5. A Bad Day at the Gallery

27:07.480 --> 27:12.480
He got the painting into the men's room and started to wash it.

27:12.480 --> 27:15.480
There was no blue ink now.

27:15.480 --> 27:20.480
But where was Mrs. Whistler's face?

27:20.480 --> 27:26.480
It was a long, difficult weekend for David. Then Monday arrived.

27:26.480 --> 27:30.480
The big day at the Grierson Gallery.

27:30.480 --> 27:34.480
In the car on the way to the gallery, David said to Mr. Bean,

27:34.480 --> 27:42.480
Whistler's mother is arriving today. There are going to be a lot of important people at the gallery.

27:42.480 --> 27:46.480
When Mr. Bean didn't answer, David looked at him.

27:46.480 --> 27:52.480
Oh, no. Mr. Bean had a cigarette lighter up his nose.

27:52.480 --> 27:59.480
Please, Dr. Bean, please! Don't do anything dangerous today, please!

27:59.480 --> 28:04.480
David said he really didn't want to lose his job.

28:04.480 --> 28:09.480
David and Mr. Bean walked into a big room in the gallery.

28:09.480 --> 28:13.480
There, at the end of the room, was Whistler's mother.

28:13.480 --> 28:17.480
Wonderful, said David, when he saw the painting.

28:17.480 --> 28:20.480
Mr. Grierson was there and smiled at him.

28:20.480 --> 28:27.480
Yes, it's very beautiful, he said. A really great work of art.

28:27.480 --> 28:32.480
Now, follow me, everybody. We've got to plan the day.

28:32.480 --> 28:34.480
He turned to Mr. Bean.

28:34.480 --> 28:41.480
Ah, good morning, Dr. Bean. Would you like to stay here and look after the painting?

28:41.480 --> 28:45.480
Ah, yes, okay.

28:45.480 --> 28:47.480
Said Mr. Bean.

28:47.480 --> 28:54.480
Then everybody left, and Mr. Bean was the only person in the room with the famous painting.

28:54.480 --> 29:00.480
He was bored. He didn't want to look after Whistler's stupid old mother.

29:00.480 --> 29:04.480
He started to walk slowly around the room.

29:04.480 --> 29:08.480
When he got near the painting, he looked at it carefully.

29:08.480 --> 29:14.480
This painting's dirty, he thought, with his face very near the painting,

29:14.480 --> 29:20.480
and then he sneezed all over the painting. Oh, dear!

29:20.480 --> 29:26.480
He quickly got his handkerchief out of his jacket and started to clean the painting.

29:27.480 --> 29:30.480
Argh! He shouted a minute later.

29:30.480 --> 29:34.480
Oh, no! How did that happen?

29:34.480 --> 29:43.480
There was now blue ink all over Mrs. Whistler's face. He looked at his handkerchief.

29:43.480 --> 29:46.480
There was wet ink on that, too.

29:46.480 --> 29:51.480
My pen, he cried, and took out his pen from his jacket.

29:51.480 --> 29:54.480
There was ink everywhere.

29:54.480 --> 29:56.480
What could he do?

29:56.480 --> 30:00.480
He thought for a minute, then took the painting off the wall.

30:00.480 --> 30:04.480
But it was very heavy and fell onto the floor.

30:04.480 --> 30:08.480
Then, by mistake, Mr. Bean stood on it.

30:08.480 --> 30:14.480
Help! He thought, this is getting worse and worse!

30:14.480 --> 30:18.480
He opened the door and looked out of the room.

30:18.480 --> 30:24.480
There was nobody there. With great difficulty, he carried the painting out of the room.

30:24.480 --> 30:28.480
The toilet, he thought, water!

30:28.480 --> 30:33.480
He got the painting into the men's room and started to wash it.

30:33.480 --> 30:39.480
There was no blue ink now, but where was Mrs. Whistler's face?

30:39.480 --> 30:42.480
Mr. Bean went hot and cold.

30:42.480 --> 30:45.480
Then he had an idea.

30:45.480 --> 30:49.480
The meeting finished, and David left the room.

30:49.480 --> 30:56.480
Right, he thought. Now I'll get Dr. Bean and have another look at our beautiful painting.

30:56.480 --> 31:01.480
But when he arrived at the room, he couldn't open the door.

31:01.480 --> 31:04.480
Dr. Bean, he shouted,

31:04.480 --> 31:09.480
There's a problem with the door! Can you open it, please?

31:09.480 --> 31:14.480
After a long time, Mr. Bean opened the door.

31:14.480 --> 31:16.480
David looked at him.

31:16.480 --> 31:19.480
Mr. Bean's face was grey.

31:19.480 --> 31:22.480
What's wrong, he asked?

31:22.480 --> 31:26.480
Erm, erm, answered Mr. Bean.

31:26.480 --> 31:29.480
What? What? cried David.

31:29.480 --> 31:32.480
Mr. Bean looked very afraid.

31:32.480 --> 31:36.480
It's erm, it's the painting.

31:36.480 --> 31:38.480
He said quietly.

31:38.480 --> 31:41.480
Where is it, shouted David?

31:41.480 --> 31:43.480
Erm, here.

31:43.480 --> 31:47.480
Said Mr. Bean. He showed David the painting.

31:47.480 --> 31:52.480
I heard a little accident, but I think it's okay now.

31:52.480 --> 31:57.480
I painted a face on her. Do you like it?

31:57.480 --> 32:02.480
David looked at the painting with wide eyes. He felt sick.

32:02.480 --> 32:07.480
Oh no, he cried. No, no, no.

32:07.480 --> 32:10.480
What are we going to do now?

32:11.480 --> 32:20.480
Chapter 6. A Good Night's Work

32:20.480 --> 32:25.480
He put the bag on his back and jumped onto Kevin's bicycle.

32:25.480 --> 32:32.480
Then he rode quickly out of the garage, into the dark.

32:32.480 --> 32:35.480
It was midnight in the Langley's house.

32:35.480 --> 32:38.480
Alison and the children were home again.

32:38.480 --> 32:43.480
They didn't want to be in the same house as the strange Doctor Bean,

32:43.480 --> 32:46.480
but the children had to go to school.

32:46.480 --> 32:49.480
David was asleep in the sitting room.

32:49.480 --> 32:54.480
Alison was very angry with him and didn't want him in the bedroom.

32:54.480 --> 33:00.480
Mr. Bean couldn't sleep. He was very unhappy.

33:00.480 --> 33:04.480
He sat in the kitchen. He thought and thought.

33:04.480 --> 33:07.480
David will lose his job now.

33:07.480 --> 33:10.480
He thought sadly.

33:10.480 --> 33:15.480
At one o'clock, Kevin walked into the kitchen. He looked sleepy.

33:15.480 --> 33:17.480
Hi, Beanie.

33:17.480 --> 33:22.480
Oh, hello, Kevin. Why aren't you in bed?

33:22.480 --> 33:29.480
I couldn't sleep. I can't stop thinking about beautiful women with no clothes on.

33:29.480 --> 33:32.480
And you? said Kevin.

33:32.480 --> 33:36.480
I can't stop thinking about Whistler's mother.

33:36.480 --> 33:38.480
answered Mr. Bean.

33:38.480 --> 33:42.480
Whistler's mother. Boring.

33:42.480 --> 33:44.480
Come up to my room, Beanie.

33:44.480 --> 33:49.480
said Kevin. I've got a great poster of Cindy Crawford up there.

33:49.480 --> 33:52.480
She's better than old Whistler's mother.

33:52.480 --> 33:56.480
Then he got a glass of milk and some chocolate cake.

33:56.480 --> 33:59.480
See you in the morning, Beanie.

33:59.480 --> 34:04.480
Kevin went back to bed. But Mr. Bean sat at the kitchen table.

34:04.480 --> 34:09.480
He started thinking again. A poster of Cindy Crawford.

34:09.480 --> 34:13.480
Really, young people today.

34:13.480 --> 34:15.480
Wait a minute.

34:15.480 --> 34:17.480
He thought.

34:17.480 --> 34:24.480
Mr. Bean suddenly had an idea. Another wonderful Mr. Bean idea.

34:24.480 --> 34:29.480
He stood up quickly and found a large bag in a cupboard.

34:29.480 --> 34:35.480
First, he ran out of the kitchen and into the bathroom with the bag in his hands.

34:35.480 --> 34:41.480
Then he went quietly into Allison's bedroom, then into the kitchen again,

34:41.480 --> 34:44.480
and then into the garage.

34:44.480 --> 34:47.480
After ten minutes, the bag was very heavy.

34:47.480 --> 34:53.480
There was a hair dryer in it, a bicycle light, some eggs, some small bottles,

34:53.480 --> 34:56.480
and a lot of other things.

34:56.480 --> 35:00.480
Next, Mr. Bean went into the sitting room.

35:00.480 --> 35:04.480
Now, where's David's card? He thought.

35:04.480 --> 35:10.480
I can't open the front door at the gallery without it.

35:10.480 --> 35:16.480
He found the card in David's jacket and put it in the bag with the other things.

35:16.480 --> 35:22.480
Then Mr. Bean put on a black shirt, black jeans and a black hat.

35:22.480 --> 35:27.480
He put the bag on his back and jumped onto Kevin's bicycle.

35:27.480 --> 35:34.480
Then he rode quickly out of the garage into the dark.

35:34.480 --> 35:39.480
Fifteen minutes later, Mr. Bean arrived at the Grierson Gallery.

35:39.480 --> 35:45.480
He opened the front door with David's card and walked quietly into the building.

35:45.480 --> 35:49.480
It was two o'clock in the morning. Nobody saw him.

35:49.480 --> 35:54.480
Now, where's the gallery shop? He thought.

35:54.480 --> 36:00.480
He found the shop on the second floor. He carefully opened the door and went in.

36:00.480 --> 36:05.480
Great, he thought, when he saw a big poster of Whistler's mother.

36:05.480 --> 36:09.480
He put the poster in his bag.

36:09.480 --> 36:16.480
He then found the room with the famous painting, the painting of Whistler's mother with the funny face.

36:16.480 --> 36:19.480
He put his bag down on the floor.

36:19.480 --> 36:23.480
Right, let's start work, he thought.

36:23.480 --> 36:30.480
It was dark in the room. Mr. Bean took Kevin's bicycle light out of the bag and turned it on.

36:30.480 --> 36:34.480
Then he took out the poster of Whistler's mother.

36:34.480 --> 36:39.480
He looked at the poster and then at the famous painting on the wall.

36:39.480 --> 36:44.480
I've got to put a new surface on the poster, he thought.

36:44.480 --> 36:48.480
Then it'll be the same as the painting.

36:48.480 --> 36:54.480
He sat on the floor and slowly started painting a new surface onto the poster.

36:54.480 --> 37:00.480
He used the eggs from the Langley's kitchen and things from Allison's bottles.

37:00.480 --> 37:03.480
It was a long, difficult job.

37:03.480 --> 37:08.480
After two hours, Mr. Bean stood up and looked at the poster.

37:08.480 --> 37:11.480
Hmm, that's better.

37:11.480 --> 37:14.480
He said with a smile on his face.

37:14.480 --> 37:19.480
He took out the hairdryer from the bag and dried the new surface.

37:19.480 --> 37:23.480
Then he carefully took the famous painting off the wall.

37:23.480 --> 37:28.480
He put the poster with the new surface on the wall in the same place.

37:28.480 --> 37:33.480
Nobody will know it's only a poster, he thought.

37:33.480 --> 37:37.480
Then Mr. Bean put everything back in his bag.

37:37.480 --> 37:43.480
He carried the bag and the old painting with the funny face out of the room.

37:43.480 --> 37:50.480
Out in the street, Mr. Bean jumped onto Kevin's bicycle and rode back to the Langley's house.

37:50.480 --> 37:53.480
It was five o'clock in the morning.

37:53.480 --> 37:58.480
A good night's work, he thought, when he got into bed.

37:58.480 --> 38:01.480
David will be happy now.

38:01.480 --> 38:08.480
Chapter 7.

38:08.480 --> 38:11.480
Clever Dr. Bean.

38:11.480 --> 38:17.480
All eyes were on the back of the painting behind Mr. Grierson.

38:17.480 --> 38:22.480
He slowly turned the painting round.

38:22.480 --> 38:28.480
The next morning, at breakfast time, David came slowly into the kitchen.

38:28.480 --> 38:32.480
His face looked old and tired.

38:32.480 --> 38:36.480
It's going to be a bad day today, he said.

38:36.480 --> 38:39.480
A very bad day.

38:39.480 --> 38:44.480
In the car, on the way to the gallery, Mr. Bean tried to talk to David.

38:44.480 --> 38:48.480
He wanted to tell him about the painting.

38:48.480 --> 38:50.480
I'm David.

38:50.480 --> 38:53.480
Don't talk to me, I hate you.

38:53.480 --> 38:55.480
Answer David angrily.

38:55.480 --> 39:00.480
But David said, Mr. Bean, quiet, shouted David.

39:00.480 --> 39:05.480
Don't say anything or I'll kill you, okay?

39:05.480 --> 39:10.480
Outside the gallery, there were a lot of cars, people and cameras.

39:10.480 --> 39:15.480
Everybody wanted to see Whistler's famous painting of his mother.

39:15.480 --> 39:23.480
Inside, in the room with the painting, there were about a hundred important people from television and the newspapers.

39:23.480 --> 39:28.480
Nobody could see the painting, they could only see the back of it.

39:28.480 --> 39:31.480
David and Mr. Bean walked into the room.

39:31.480 --> 39:35.480
David wanted to find Mr. Grierson as quickly as possible.

39:35.480 --> 39:39.480
He had to tell him about the accident with the painting.

39:39.480 --> 39:41.480
Oh, David!

39:41.480 --> 39:43.480
Said Mr. Grierson.

39:43.480 --> 39:46.480
And Dr. Bean, late again.

39:46.480 --> 39:50.480
Sorry sir, a problem at home.

39:50.480 --> 39:53.480
Please sir, I've got to talk to you.

39:53.480 --> 39:55.480
Now, it's very important.

39:55.480 --> 39:57.480
Not now, David.

39:57.480 --> 39:59.480
Mr. Grierson answered.

39:59.480 --> 40:00.480
Everybody's waiting.

40:00.480 --> 40:03.480
We've got to show them the painting.

40:03.480 --> 40:05.480
But sir, cried David.

40:05.480 --> 40:08.480
It's about the painting.

40:08.480 --> 40:11.480
But Mr. Grierson didn't listen.

40:11.480 --> 40:13.480
Mr. Bean looked at David.

40:13.480 --> 40:15.480
Ah, David.

40:15.480 --> 40:19.480
Bean, go away, David said.

40:19.480 --> 40:22.480
Mr. Grierson walked to the front of the room.

40:22.480 --> 40:25.480
Good morning everybody, he said.

40:25.480 --> 40:30.480
This is a great day for America and for Whistler's mother.

40:30.480 --> 40:36.480
I won't say too much because I know you all want to see our famous painting.

40:36.480 --> 40:39.480
And here it is.

40:39.480 --> 40:42.480
David shut his eyes.

40:42.480 --> 40:45.480
I'm going to be sick, he thought.

40:45.480 --> 40:48.480
There wasn't a sound in the room.

40:48.480 --> 40:53.480
All eyes were on the back of the painting behind Mr. Grierson.

40:53.480 --> 40:57.480
He slowly turned the painting round.

40:57.480 --> 41:02.480
David stood at the back of the room next to Mr. Bean.

41:02.480 --> 41:04.480
He didn't understand.

41:04.480 --> 41:07.480
The painting looked wonderful.

41:07.480 --> 41:10.480
No blue ink, no funny face.

41:10.480 --> 41:13.480
There was nothing wrong with it.

41:13.480 --> 41:16.480
What? What did you do, Bean?

41:16.480 --> 41:18.480
He said quietly.

41:18.480 --> 41:21.480
You're wonderful, I love you.

41:21.480 --> 41:24.480
Easy, said Mr. Bean.

41:24.480 --> 41:27.480
It's a poster.

41:27.480 --> 41:30.480
It's a what, but...

41:30.480 --> 41:32.480
Shhh.

41:32.480 --> 41:34.480
Somebody will hear.

41:34.480 --> 41:37.480
But how did you do it?

41:37.480 --> 41:42.480
I came here in the middle of the night and took a poster from the shop.

41:42.480 --> 41:44.480
Said Mr. Bean.

41:44.480 --> 41:47.480
I painted a new surface on it with eggs and things.

41:47.480 --> 41:50.480
Then I dried it with a hair dryer.

41:50.480 --> 41:52.480
What's the problem?

41:52.480 --> 41:55.480
But you can't.

41:55.480 --> 41:56.480
Shhh.

41:56.480 --> 41:58.480
Don't tell anybody.

41:58.480 --> 41:59.480
Love Mr. Bean.

41:59.480 --> 42:03.480
Nobody will know it's only a poster.

42:05.480 --> 42:08.480
Dr. Bean, are you ready?

42:08.480 --> 42:10.480
Ask Mr. Grayson.

42:10.480 --> 42:13.480
Mr. Bean didn't understand.

42:13.480 --> 42:15.480
Ready for what?

42:15.480 --> 42:17.480
He asked.

42:17.480 --> 42:19.480
You're going to say something to these people.

42:19.480 --> 42:21.480
Don't you remember?

42:21.480 --> 42:23.480
What shall I talk about?

42:23.480 --> 42:26.480
About the painting, of course.

42:26.480 --> 42:28.480
Laughed Mr. Grayson.

42:28.480 --> 42:31.480
This man was very strange.

42:31.480 --> 42:34.480
Ah, yes, of course.

42:34.480 --> 42:36.480
Said Mr. Bean.

42:36.480 --> 42:40.480
He went to the front of the room and smiled at the people and cameras.

42:40.480 --> 42:43.480
What did they want him to see?

42:43.480 --> 42:46.480
We're ready, said Mr. Grayson.

42:46.480 --> 42:49.480
You can start now.

42:49.480 --> 42:55.480
Erm, erm, erm, erm...

42:55.480 --> 42:57.480
Thank you.

42:57.480 --> 43:00.480
And, hello, everybody.

43:00.480 --> 43:02.480
I'm Mr....

43:02.480 --> 43:04.480
Sorry.

43:04.480 --> 43:06.480
Dr. Bean.

43:06.480 --> 43:11.480
And I work at the National Gallery in London.

43:11.480 --> 43:17.480
I sit and look at paintings all day.

43:17.480 --> 43:19.480
Everybody liked that.

43:19.480 --> 43:21.480
They all smiled.

43:21.480 --> 43:24.480
He's very intelligent, they thought.

43:24.480 --> 43:29.480
Now, what can I say about this painting?

43:29.480 --> 43:31.480
Said Mr. Bean.

43:31.480 --> 43:34.480
She looked at the famous Whistler's mother.

43:34.480 --> 43:39.480
First, it's erm...

43:39.480 --> 43:41.480
Very big.

43:41.480 --> 43:44.480
I like big paintings.

43:44.480 --> 43:46.480
Very clever.

43:46.480 --> 43:50.480
This man from London was really good.

43:50.480 --> 43:52.480
Next.

43:52.480 --> 43:55.480
And I'm nearly at the end now.

43:55.480 --> 43:59.480
Next is the big question.

43:59.480 --> 44:07.480
Why did this gallery pay thousands of dollars for this painting?

44:07.480 --> 44:10.480
Mr. Bean looked at David.

44:10.480 --> 44:14.480
But David couldn't help him now.

44:14.480 --> 44:17.480
And the answer is...

44:17.480 --> 44:20.480
Erm...

44:20.480 --> 44:23.480
What is the answer?

44:23.480 --> 44:28.480
This painting is expensive because...

44:28.480 --> 44:34.480
It's a picture of Whistler's mother.

44:34.480 --> 44:40.480
And I know that families are very important.

44:40.480 --> 44:49.480
I know that because I'm staying with my best friend, David, and his lovely family.

44:49.480 --> 44:54.480
Whistler's mother wasn't a beautiful woman.

44:54.480 --> 44:56.480
Look at the painting.

44:56.480 --> 44:59.480
She's an ugly old thing.

44:59.480 --> 45:02.480
But she was his mother.

45:02.480 --> 45:05.480
And he loved her.

45:05.480 --> 45:09.480
And I think that's wonderful.

45:09.480 --> 45:11.480
Everybody stood up.

45:11.480 --> 45:14.480
Thank you, Dr. Bean.

45:14.480 --> 45:16.480
Another photo, please.

45:16.480 --> 45:18.480
Look this way, Dr. Bean.

45:18.480 --> 45:21.480
Mr. Bean was famous.

45:21.480 --> 45:24.480
And David was very, very happy.

45:24.480 --> 45:30.480
But before David and Mr. Bean could leave the room, a policeman came in.

45:30.480 --> 45:31.480
Mr. Langley?

45:31.480 --> 45:35.480
He said to David, can I talk to you, sir?

45:35.480 --> 45:37.480
David looked at Mr. Bean.

45:37.480 --> 45:40.480
He was suddenly very afraid.

45:40.480 --> 45:44.480
It's okay, he said to the policeman quickly.

45:44.480 --> 45:47.480
I'll tell you everything.

45:47.480 --> 45:49.480
Everything?

45:49.480 --> 45:52.480
Yes, everything about the painting.

45:53.480 --> 45:54.480
What painting?

45:54.480 --> 45:57.480
I don't want to talk about a painting, said the policeman.

45:57.480 --> 45:59.480
I'm sorry, Mr. Langley.

45:59.480 --> 46:01.480
It's your daughter.

46:01.480 --> 46:02.480
She's in hospital.

46:02.480 --> 46:05.480
A road accident, sir.

46:09.480 --> 46:10.480
Chapter 8.

46:10.480 --> 46:13.480
At the hospital.

46:13.480 --> 46:17.480
He really wanted that, sweet.

46:17.480 --> 46:22.480
Slowly, he put his hand into the man's stomach.

46:22.480 --> 46:27.480
He found the sweet and took it out.

46:27.480 --> 46:30.480
The hospital was very busy.

46:30.480 --> 46:34.480
David and Mr. Bean ran quickly to the front desk.

46:34.480 --> 46:36.480
Excuse me, David said.

46:36.480 --> 46:39.480
Can you tell me my daughter's room number?

46:39.480 --> 46:43.480
Jennifer Langley, she came in at about one o'clock.

46:43.480 --> 46:45.480
A road accident.

46:45.480 --> 46:47.480
One minute, sir.

46:47.480 --> 46:49.480
Said the woman at the desk.

46:49.480 --> 46:51.480
Ah, yes.

46:51.480 --> 46:54.480
She's in room 106.

46:54.480 --> 46:56.480
David ran up the stairs.

46:56.480 --> 46:58.480
Mr. Bean followed him.

46:58.480 --> 47:00.480
No, Bean, shouted David.

47:00.480 --> 47:03.480
You stay there and do nothing.

47:03.480 --> 47:04.480
Nothing.

47:04.480 --> 47:07.480
Then nothing can go wrong.

47:07.480 --> 47:09.480
Mr. Bean understood.

47:09.480 --> 47:12.480
He watched David leave.

47:12.480 --> 47:14.480
He felt very sad.

47:14.480 --> 47:16.480
He wanted to help.

47:16.480 --> 47:19.480
And he wanted a family, too.

47:19.480 --> 47:22.480
David found room 106 and went in.

47:22.480 --> 47:27.480
Jennifer was in bed and Alison was on a chair next to her.

47:27.480 --> 47:30.480
Ali, how is she?

47:30.480 --> 47:33.480
Oh, David, I don't know.

47:33.480 --> 47:34.480
Cried Alison.

47:34.480 --> 47:38.480
I'm waiting for the doctor.

47:38.480 --> 47:41.480
Mr. Bean sat and waited for David.

47:41.480 --> 47:46.480
After some time, he felt bored and started to walk around the hospital.

47:46.480 --> 47:50.480
A doctor suddenly ran out of a room and saw Mr. Bean.

47:50.480 --> 47:52.480
Who are you?

47:52.480 --> 47:53.480
He asked.

47:53.480 --> 47:54.480
Me.

47:54.480 --> 47:56.480
I'm Dr. Bean.

47:56.480 --> 47:57.480
Good.

47:57.480 --> 47:59.480
I'm Dr. Jacobson.

47:59.480 --> 48:01.480
I want some help, Dr. come with me.

48:01.480 --> 48:03.480
Oh, no.

48:03.480 --> 48:06.480
Mr. Bean wasn't really a doctor.

48:06.480 --> 48:09.480
He was only Dr. Bean at the Grierson Gallery.

48:09.480 --> 48:12.480
Not in a hospital.

48:12.480 --> 48:18.480
I'm really Mr. Bean, not doctor.

48:18.480 --> 48:21.480
He said that Dr. Jacobson was too busy.

48:21.480 --> 48:23.480
He didn't hear him.

48:23.480 --> 48:27.480
Mr. Bean followed Dr. Jacobson into an operating room.

48:27.480 --> 48:29.480
Okay, listen everybody.

48:29.480 --> 48:31.480
This is Dr. Bean.

48:31.480 --> 48:34.480
Doctor, this man's got a bullet in his stomach.

48:34.480 --> 48:36.480
It's bad.

48:36.480 --> 48:41.480
I've got another operation in room four, but I'll see you later.

48:41.480 --> 48:47.480
Dr. Jacobson ran out of the operating room and everybody looked at Dr. Bean.

48:47.480 --> 48:49.480
Here, doctor.

48:49.480 --> 48:52.480
Put these clothes on, somebody said.

48:52.480 --> 48:55.480
Doctor, this man's dying.

48:55.480 --> 49:02.480
Do something fast, another person said.

49:02.480 --> 49:05.480
Mr. Bean didn't answer.

49:05.480 --> 49:08.480
Shall I make the first cut, Dr. Bean?

49:08.480 --> 49:10.480
Asked a very young doctor.

49:10.480 --> 49:11.480
Okay.

49:11.480 --> 49:13.480
Said Mr. Bean.

49:13.480 --> 49:16.480
He felt very, very afraid.

49:16.480 --> 49:21.480
The young doctor started to cut open the man's stomach.

49:21.480 --> 49:25.480
Mr. Bean watched and felt very sick.

49:25.480 --> 49:28.480
Suddenly, somebody outside shouted,

49:28.480 --> 49:30.480
Quick! Help!

49:30.480 --> 49:33.480
We're losing her! Help!

49:33.480 --> 49:41.480
Everybody in the operating room ran out and Mr. Bean was the only person in the room again.

49:41.480 --> 49:46.480
He waited for the other people, but nobody came back.

49:46.480 --> 49:50.480
After some time, he took out a packet of sweets.

49:50.480 --> 49:55.480
He threw a sweet up into the air and tried to catch it in his mouth.

49:55.480 --> 50:00.480
But the sweet fell into the stomach of the man on the operating table.

50:01.480 --> 50:03.480
Mr. Bean looked down.

50:03.480 --> 50:06.480
He really wanted that sweet.

50:06.480 --> 50:11.480
Slowly, he put his hand into the man's stomach.

50:11.480 --> 50:15.480
He found the sweet and took it out.

50:15.480 --> 50:20.480
But it wasn't his sweet, it was the bullet.

50:20.480 --> 50:24.480
Mr. Bean was hungry, but he couldn't eat a bullet.

50:24.480 --> 50:29.480
He quickly put it back into the man's stomach and then found his sweet.

50:30.480 --> 50:34.480
He washed it and put it into his mouth.

50:34.480 --> 50:37.480
Mmm, lovely.

50:37.480 --> 50:42.480
A minute later, everybody ran back into the operating room.

50:42.480 --> 50:47.480
Okay, let's find that bullet, said the young doctor.

50:47.480 --> 50:50.480
He looked in the man's stomach, but he couldn't see it.

50:50.480 --> 50:54.480
I can't see anything. Where is that bullet?

50:54.480 --> 50:58.480
We'll have to find it, or he's a dead man.

50:59.480 --> 51:01.480
Mr. Bean watched him.

51:01.480 --> 51:04.480
He thought for a minute and then said,

51:04.480 --> 51:08.480
No problem, here, I'll do it.

51:08.480 --> 51:11.480
He carefully put his hands into the man's stomach.

51:11.480 --> 51:13.480
Everybody shouted,

51:13.480 --> 51:16.480
Stop, you can't do that.

51:16.480 --> 51:19.480
Take your hands out, it's too dangerous.

51:19.480 --> 51:22.480
Mr. Bean didn't listen.

51:22.480 --> 51:26.480
He took his hands out of the man's stomach and smiled.

51:26.480 --> 51:29.480
He showed them the bullet.

51:29.480 --> 51:32.480
What? I don't understand.

51:32.480 --> 51:34.480
Cried the young doctor.

51:34.480 --> 51:36.480
Wonderful, wonderful.

51:36.480 --> 51:41.480
They all shouted, Dr. Bean's the cleverest doctor in the world.

51:46.480 --> 51:48.480
Chapter 9

51:48.480 --> 51:52.480
We love you, Mr. Bean.

51:52.480 --> 51:56.480
Yes, it's me, he said.

51:56.480 --> 52:02.480
And I'd like to stay with you in Los Angeles for another week.

52:03.480 --> 52:09.480
Five minutes later, Mr. Bean walked out of the operating room in his blue doctor's clothes.

52:09.480 --> 52:13.480
Phew, I'd like a cup of coffee, he thought.

52:13.480 --> 52:16.480
Suddenly, somebody behind him shouted,

52:16.480 --> 52:18.480
Doctor, Doctor!

52:18.480 --> 52:19.480
Oh no!

52:19.480 --> 52:22.480
Thought Mr. Bean, not again.

52:22.480 --> 52:26.480
He turned round, and there was David.

52:26.480 --> 52:29.480
Doctor, come quickly, it's my daughter.

52:29.480 --> 52:33.480
She's in room 106, quick!

52:33.480 --> 52:35.480
Mr. Bean couldn't say no.

52:35.480 --> 52:38.480
He had to go and see Jennifer.

52:38.480 --> 52:39.480
Oh, Doctor!

52:39.480 --> 52:43.480
Cried Allison when she saw Mr. Bean in his doctor's clothes.

52:43.480 --> 52:46.480
Quick, do something!

52:47.480 --> 52:50.480
Mr. Bean looked at Jennifer on the bed.

52:50.480 --> 52:53.480
Oh, Mr. and Mrs.

52:53.480 --> 52:59.480
He started to say, Langley said David and Allison.

52:59.480 --> 53:12.480
Yes, Mr. and Mrs. Langley, your daughter's going to be fine, but I'd like to see her without you here.

53:13.480 --> 53:17.480
Of course, Doctor, they said, and left quickly.

53:17.480 --> 53:22.480
Mr. Bean was the only person in the room, again.

53:22.480 --> 53:25.480
Everything was very quiet.

53:25.480 --> 53:28.480
Not a sound.

53:28.480 --> 53:32.480
Mr. Bean slowly went to Jennifer's bed.

53:32.480 --> 53:34.480
Jennifer!

53:34.480 --> 53:38.480
He said, Wake up!

53:38.480 --> 53:41.480
Wake up!

53:41.480 --> 53:43.480
Wake up!

53:43.480 --> 53:45.480
Jennifer didn't open her eyes.

53:45.480 --> 53:50.480
Mr. Bean sat on the bed and put his face near Jennifer's.

53:50.480 --> 53:53.480
Then he started making funny faces.

53:53.480 --> 53:55.480
Blah!

53:55.480 --> 53:58.480
He shouted, Lang!

53:58.480 --> 54:01.480
Jennifer didn't move.

54:01.480 --> 54:04.480
Next, Mr. Bean hit her.

54:04.480 --> 54:06.480
Nothing happened.

54:07.480 --> 54:11.480
He climbed onto her bed and looked down at her.

54:11.480 --> 54:14.480
Then he jumped on top of her, hard.

54:14.480 --> 54:17.480
And Jennifer woke up.

54:17.480 --> 54:19.480
Dad! Mom! Help!

54:19.480 --> 54:21.480
She shouted.

54:21.480 --> 54:24.480
Mr. Bean got off the bed quickly.

54:24.480 --> 54:27.480
Outside, David and Allison heard their daughter.

54:27.480 --> 54:31.480
They ran into the room as fast as they could.

54:31.480 --> 54:32.480
Jennifer!

54:33.480 --> 54:35.480
You're okay!

54:35.480 --> 54:37.480
What happened, Mom?

54:37.480 --> 54:40.480
Jennifer asked. Her eyes were wide open now.

54:40.480 --> 54:42.480
You had an accident, dear.

54:42.480 --> 54:46.480
But everything's going to be okay now.

54:46.480 --> 54:51.480
Mr. Bean watched the happy family, then walked to the door.

54:51.480 --> 54:53.480
David looked round.

54:53.480 --> 54:55.480
Doctor, don't go!

54:55.480 --> 54:59.480
He said to Mr. Bean with a smile on his face.

54:59.480 --> 55:01.480
Oh, a little girl's okay.

55:01.480 --> 55:04.480
And we want to thank you, Doctor.

55:04.480 --> 55:08.480
Yes, Doctor, thank you a thousand times, said Allison.

55:08.480 --> 55:10.480
What can we do for you now?

55:10.480 --> 55:15.480
We want to thank you. We'll do anything, anything.

55:15.480 --> 55:18.480
Mr. Bean thought for a minute.

55:18.480 --> 55:21.480
Then he took off his doctor's clothes.

55:21.480 --> 55:24.480
It's Mr. Bean, they shouted.

55:24.480 --> 55:27.480
Yes, it's me, he said.

55:27.480 --> 55:33.480
And I'd like to stay with you in Los Angeles for another week.

55:33.480 --> 55:37.480
Another week with this strange Englishman.

55:37.480 --> 55:40.480
Strange, but wonderful, too.

55:40.480 --> 55:44.480
Yes, Mr. Bean was a friend now.

55:44.480 --> 55:47.480
Of course, they all shouted.

55:47.480 --> 55:50.480
We love you, Mr. Bean.

55:51.480 --> 55:54.480
Chapter 10.

55:54.480 --> 55:59.480
It's a poster.

55:59.480 --> 56:02.480
Mr. Bean got into bed.

56:02.480 --> 56:10.480
Before he went to sleep, he looked up at the wall opposite his bed and smiled.

56:10.480 --> 56:14.480
Mr. Bean had a great week in Los Angeles.

56:14.480 --> 56:17.480
There were only one or two accidents.

56:18.480 --> 56:23.480
The time went quickly, and then it was the end of his holiday in America.

56:23.480 --> 56:27.480
On his last day with the Langleys, they had a big party,

56:27.480 --> 56:31.480
and Mr. Bean took more photos of everybody.

56:31.480 --> 56:34.480
Then they had to say goodbye.

56:34.480 --> 56:39.480
Goodbye, dear Mr. Bean, said Allison and the children outside the house.

56:39.480 --> 56:42.480
Please come and visit us again.

56:43.480 --> 56:45.480
Goodbye, everybody.

56:45.480 --> 56:50.480
Thank you very much for my lovely holiday.

56:50.480 --> 56:53.480
David drove Mr. Bean to the airport.

56:53.480 --> 56:57.480
There were no policemen there with guns this time.

56:57.480 --> 57:02.480
Well, goodbye Beanie, said David, and put his arm round him.

57:02.480 --> 57:09.480
Have a good journey back to England, and come back sometime in the future.

57:09.480 --> 57:14.480
David liked Mr. Bean, but he remembered the bad times too.

57:14.480 --> 57:17.480
Goodbye, David, said Mr. Bean.

57:17.480 --> 57:20.480
Thank you for everything.

57:20.480 --> 57:23.480
Mr. Bean turned and walked away.

57:23.480 --> 57:27.480
David watched him, and then left the airport.

57:27.480 --> 57:30.480
Suddenly, he felt somebody behind him.

57:30.480 --> 57:34.480
He turned round, and there was Mr. Bean.

57:34.480 --> 57:40.480
Mr. Bean wanted to take one last photo, and to put his arms round David too.

57:40.480 --> 57:44.480
Then he was ready to leave America.

57:44.480 --> 57:50.480
Three years later, Mr. Bean sat in his little house in England

57:50.480 --> 57:54.480
and thought about his wonderful holiday in America.

57:54.480 --> 57:59.480
Before he went to bed, he looked at the photos of his good friends, the Langleys,

57:59.480 --> 58:01.480
on his sitting-room wall.

58:01.480 --> 58:03.480
He smiled.

58:03.480 --> 58:07.480
In Los Angeles, it was a beautiful afternoon.

58:07.480 --> 58:11.480
At the Grierson Gallery, David sat in the room with Whistler's mother

58:11.480 --> 58:15.480
and thought about his strange friend, Mr. Bean.

58:15.480 --> 58:19.480
He looked at the famous painting and laughed.

58:19.480 --> 58:23.480
Suddenly, his cup of coffee began to move across the table.

58:23.480 --> 58:27.480
Then the painting began to move too.

58:27.480 --> 58:30.480
Oh, no! cried David.

58:30.480 --> 58:33.480
Mr. Grierson ran into the room.

58:33.480 --> 58:35.480
The ground's moving, David!

58:35.480 --> 58:36.480
He shouted.

58:36.480 --> 58:37.480
The paintings!

58:37.480 --> 58:41.480
Why are we going to do about the paintings?

58:41.480 --> 58:46.480
Before David could answer, Whistler's mother fell off the wall.

58:46.480 --> 58:50.480
Mr. Grierson looked at the painting on the floor.

58:50.480 --> 58:51.480
No!

58:51.480 --> 58:52.480
No!

58:52.480 --> 58:53.480
He suddenly cried out.

58:53.480 --> 58:56.480
Look! David, look!

58:56.480 --> 58:58.480
David looked down.

58:58.480 --> 59:03.480
On the back of the painting were the words, Whistler's mother,

59:03.480 --> 59:06.480
a Grierson Gallery poster.

59:06.480 --> 59:09.480
It's a poster, David!

59:09.480 --> 59:10.480
A poster!

59:10.480 --> 59:15.480
So, so where's the painting?

59:15.480 --> 59:20.480
In England, Mr. Bean got into bed.

59:20.480 --> 59:25.480
Before he went to sleep, he looked up at the wall opposite his bed and smiled.

59:25.480 --> 59:31.480
Good night, old dear, he said, and turned off the light.

59:31.480 --> 59:34.480
What was on the wall?

59:34.480 --> 59:40.480
The famous painting, Whistler's mother, of course, with the funny face.

